    <bf:title>
      <bf:Title>
	<bf:mainTitle>History of Texas Indians</bf:mainTitle>
	<bf:partName>From the plains, Texas buffalo hunters and warriors</bf:partName>
      </bf:Title>
    </bf:title>
    <bf:title>
      <bf:VariantTitle>
	<rdf:type rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/vartitletype/por"/>
	<bf:mainTitle>Texas buffalo hunters and warriors</bf:mainTitle>
      </bf:VariantTitle>
    </bf:title>
    <bf:summary>
      <bf:Summary>
	<rdfs:label>Presents "the pre-horse distribution of the Indian tribes and the geographical/environmental nature of their home on the southern Great Plains. Reveals the challenges to the Indian way of life with the coming of the Europeans and the introduction of the horse. Chronicles the rise and fall of the Comanches and Kiowa"--SVE Website.</rdfs:label>
      </bf:Summary>
    </bf:summary>
